<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Baebi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've not been here in a while. I took a long break from EQ. I'm sure there have been some discussions on this before but I didn't find them when I searched. Would you all be so kind as to explain what you've found out about this spell and when the best times are to use it?<P>Thanks Baebi<BR>Just barely 51</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Burro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Best time: never<P>Burro<BR>Erollisi Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Costs: 1 pearl, 1 buff slot, and 100 mana<BR>Benefits: None<P>also wont stack with strength spells I dont think but on the bright side if you trade it in you might get a useful spell back</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kitsinu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It is a potentially useful crap buff.  Though 5 platinum for a crap buff seems a bit excessive...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Salina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have to agree..<P>Although it was hilarious tonight.. we killed Yael in the Hole, and both clerics survived.<P>So we had all buffed with DP just in case, due to our low numbers we hoped maybe *MAYBE* DP would save someone from a DT.<P>At any rate, after the fight, our other cleric was manastoning.. and his DP went off.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR>Salina Grey<BR>Erudite Templar of Pain, Bertoxxulous<BR>Guild Leader, Glory's Path</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morgan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Many, many, many attempts.  Never, ever been successful.  I still use it before every huge battle...thinking one day it may actually work  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Walbort</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I used it often, and saw it save several people. When everything rides on the survival of your enchanter, I saw no point in not sticking it on there.<P>And it saved me from stoning to death once too. :/</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KamuelaTZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">An old cleric friend of mine said it has ALWAYS worked on the enchanter. For everyone else it is a crap shoot.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trilvan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">There is speculation that either your charisma or the charisma of the person you are casting it on has a lot to do with whether it will go off or not. I do not know if that is true or not but worth mentioning.<P>------------------<BR>Trilvan Lostheart<BR>41st Cleric of Love Peace and Happiness</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've rarely seen it go off, and I personally have never seen it go off and actually save anybody.  If the fits hitting the shan, it's too little, too late in my opinion, so I haven't cast it in a very long time.  The upgrade, Divine Intervention, is even worse.  500 mana, 2 emeralds (17ppx2), and a 2 or 3 minute recast with only a 10 minute duration...ugh.  I tried it like 6 times on 2 main tanks for really big battles, and I tried maxing my charisma (based on those rumors about the casters charisma mattering, I had a 185ish charisma when cast) and I've never seen DI go off in my 6 attempts at using it.  It's one of those spells that could have been really really good, but it's just too costly in pp, mana, and too short in duration and actual effectiveness to even bother with it.<P>Dalain</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KamuelaTZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I believe it is the charisma of the recipient. Otherwise, what happens if the caster camps? Storing the data of the stats of the caster for a buff seems too ridiculous even for Verant.<P>Why does it fail? The buff has the most use on tanks. Tanks focus on nearly everything other than charisma. Most tanks are large races and have a charisma below 75. Remember how important 75agi is to your AC?<P>I've seen pact work on an enchanter in a raid, he had 200cha. I've never seen it work on a 'fatty' and it sounds like others have little success with it. The only warrior race with 75+ charisma base is human I believe. Add to that highelf, woodelf, human, and maybe erudite hybrids?<P>Verant makes a lot of SNAFUs. Maybe this is one of them, or maybe melee classes need to realize that charisma is not a useless stat.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morganna Dragonsveil</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Uhmm, it's a check on the "caster's" Charisma when casting Death Pact that will determine it's going off.<P>Had a Shaman charisma buff me to 141 Charisma once when I was casting DP on whole group. (was killing Overking and Queen).<P>Well, what can I say? All 6 DP went off :0 'nuff said<P>------------------<BR>Morganna Dragonsveil<BR>Harbinger of Storms<BR>Holy Bucket of Rodcet Nife</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">So, could someone define "DP goes off" for me. What exactly does it do?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Salina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It gives a message of "Soandso's death pact has been benevolently fulfilled" and heals the person about 200 points.<P>Not terribly useful, but it might come in handy as a saver... if/when it works.<P>------------------<BR>Salina Grey<BR>Erudite Templar of Pain, Bertoxxulous<BR>Guild Leader, Glory's Path</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
